headline: Is a Major Chainsaw Recall Revealing New Supply Chain Risks for Home Depot (HD)?
summary: Earlier this month, Home Depot issued a voluntary recall of nearly 98,000 Milwaukee Tool M18 FUEL Top Handle Chainsaws sold in the US and Canada due to reported brake safety component failures, including one injury. This large-scale product recall, prompted by safety concerns, highlights operational and reputational risks that can arise from issues in Home Depot’s supplier relationships and quality assurance processes.
